      <h1>Bactrian camels, the survivors of the Silk Route, are plying a new trade in Ladakh</h1>
      <h2>The double-humped camel was on the verge of extinction in India. A commercial initiative, disliked by activists, has helped revive their population.</h2>
      <!-- MOBILE & TABLET ONLY META-->
      
